						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Undated. In Tamiḻ-Brāhmi characters. (2nd cent. B.C.).</hi></p>						

						<p>Inscriptions from 70 to 76 probably comprise one single inscription engraved in a long line. All the eight persons named in these inscriptions seem to be collectively endowded the execution of the drip ledge <hi rend="italic">(tāra aṇi)</hi> of the cavern, which is mentioned in the sixth segment (No. 75).</p>						

						<p>The following inscription (first segment) has been split into three segments in <hi rend="italic">ETE.</hi> (2014). Mentions that Viyakaṉ Gaṇatikaṉ, a salt merchant from Mattirai (Madurai) has endowed the drip ledge of the rock shelter. At the end of the name is a crab like symbol.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">ETE.</hi> (2014)., Nos. 38-40, pp. 431-435.</p>						

						</summary>
